sql:
SELECT AVG(gpa) AS average_gpa
FROM students
WHERE major = 'Computer Science';

external_knowledge:
- "Latest academic journey" refers to the most recent enrollment of each student;
- "Path they tread" refers to the courses they have taken;
- "Seasons of their terms" refers to the term descriptions (e.g., Fall Semester 2005);
- "Grades they harvested" refers to the grades they received.

- "course title" refers to the name of the course;
- "average grade" is the mean grade received by students in the course;
- "garden" is a metaphor for the course, and "flowers blooming" represents the grades students receive.

- "Journey of student enrollments" refers to the progression of enrollments over different academic terms;
- "Cumulative number of students" is the total number of students who have enrolled in a course up to a given term;
- "Maximum allowed enrollment" is the capacity limit set for each section;
- "Actual enrollment" is the number of students currently enrolled in a section.

